    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound driver\u2019s car featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six with VarioCam Plus timing. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a dry rear main seal. Notably, the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a ceramic dual-row upgrade, mitigating common M96 architecture concerns. The chassis maintains excellent lateral stiffness through its multi-link rear geometry and MacPherson front struts. Stopping power is provided by four-piston Brembo Monobloc calipers over ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. While the finish shows light road patina, the engine exhibits strong compression and a linear torque curve, making it an ideal candidate for spirited touring or club events.",
